SIMPLE: broke
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Broke
<hw>Broke</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Broker</er>, and cf. <er>Brook</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
transact business for another.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Brome.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To act as procurer in love matters; to pimp.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We do want a certain necessary woman to <qex>broke</qex> between
them, Cupid said.</q> <rj><qau>Fanshawe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>brokes</qex> with all that can in such a suit⟦br⟧
Corrupt the tender honor of a maid.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 184 --></p>

<p><ent>Broke</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Broke
<hw>Broke</hw> <pr>(br⟦omac⟧k)</pr>, <def><pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> of
<er>Break</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Broken</ent>⟦br⟧
